Digital Egypt for Universities
Homepage Timeline Maps AZ index Learning Digital Egypt for Universities A learning and teaching resource for higher education A learning and teaching resource developed in at for the Petrie Museum of Egyptian Archaeology funded by with 3000 pages created by Wolfram Grajetzki 300 pages by Stephen Quirke and invited contributors 
3 d reconstructions of 14 archaeological sites by Narushige Shiode This site is aimed to assist teaching across all disciplines and was created in 20002003 managed by Stephen Quirke The Petrie Museum aims to provide translations of the site in Arabic and Spanish for information and suggestions on funding please contact Stephen Quirke Copyright  2000 University College London. All rights reserved.